<script id="audio-player-live-event-listener" type="text/javascript">
  // submits an event when the audio player live starts playing
  // also sends an event every minute thereafter as long as the audio player
  // is not paused
    (function(document, window, undefined) {
      
      var $;
      var setInt = setTimeout(poll, 1000);
      var timeOut = 0;
      
      //check if jQuery is available
      //if not available, check again every second for 5 seconds
      function poll() {
        if (window.jQuery) {
          $ = window.jQuery;
          clearTimeout(setInt);
          init();
        } else if (timeOut > 5) {
          clearTimeout(setInt);
        } else {
          timeOut++;
        }
      }
      
      
      function init() {
        
        // set variable for interval
        var setIntVar;
        // increment this every minute when the player is playing
        var playTime = 0;
        // set to true if the start event has already fired
        var hasStarted = false;

        // if the player is playing at the minute check, send a custom event
        var sendTimingEvent = function() {
          window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
            'eventAction':playTime + ' minutes',
            'event': 'mip_Audio_Live'
          });
          playTime++;
        };

        // if the play button is checked, switch isPlaying to true
        $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.play, function(event) {
          if (!hasStarted) {
            window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
              'eventAction':'start',
              'event': 'mip_Audio_Live'
            });
            hasStarted = false;
            playTime++;
          }
          setIntVar = setInterval(sendTimingEvent, 1000*60);
        });


        // if the pause button is pressed, clear the setInterval
        $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.pause, function(event) {
          window.clearInterval(setIntVar);
        });


        // if the end is reached, clear the setInterval
        $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.end, function(event) {
          window.clearInterval(setIntVar);
        });
        
      }
      



    })(document, window);
  </script>

<script id="audio-player-article-event-listener" type="text/javascript">
  // Watches for play and end in article audio players and submits a data layer event
  // also submits a data layer event at the 10%, 25%, 50%, 75%, and 90% marks of the audio file
  (function(document) {
    
      var $;
      var setInt = setTimeout(poll, 1000);
      var timeOut = 0;
      
      //check if jQuery is available
      //if not available, check again every second for 5 seconds
      function poll() {
        if (window.jQuery) {
          $ = window.jQuery;
          clearTimeout(setInt);
          init();
        } else if (timeOut > 5) {
          clearTimeout(setInt);
        } else {
          timeOut++;
        }
      }

      
    function init() {
    
      // returns the title of the audio clip
      var getTitle = function() {
        try {
          var playerTag = document.querySelectorAll(".story-audio");
          var aTag = playerTag[0].getElementsByTagName("a");
          return $(aTag[0]).attr("title");
        }
        catch (e) {
          return "";
        }
      };

      // create object to track if duration events have already been sent
      var played = {};

      // list of duration percentages that we want to track
      var marks = {
        '10%' : 0.1,
        '25%' : 0.25,
        '50%' : 0.5,
        '75%' : 0.75,
        '90%' : 0.9
      };

      //check if the play event has been sent
      var hasStarted = false;


      //tracks when the player is started
      $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.play, function(event) {
        //track it as an event with category:Audio, action:start, label:video title
        if (!hasStarted) {
          window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
            'eventCategory' : 'Audio',
            'eventAction' : 'start',
            'eventLabel' : getTitle(),
            'event' : 'mip_Audio_Article'
          });
          hasStarted = true;
        }
      });


      //tracks percentage played

      $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.timeupdate, function(event) {
        var status = event.jPlayer.status;
        var percentTime = status.currentTime / status.duration;

        // only checks for duration played every second (instead of every quarter second)
        if (status.currentTime % 1 < .2) {
          

          // sends custom event if the percentage played is close to the cutoff
          for (var key in marks) {
              if ( marks[key] <= percentTime && !played[key]) {
                 played[key] = true;
                 window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
                  'eventCategory' : 'Audio',
                  'eventAction' : key,
                  'eventLabel' : getTitle(),
                  'event' : 'mip_Audio_Article'
                 });
            }
          }
        }



      });

      // tracks when player ends
      $("#jquery_jplayer_1").bind($.jPlayer.event.ended, function(event) {
          window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
            'eventCategory' : 'Audio',
            'eventAction' : 'end',
            'eventLabel' : getTitle(),
            'event' : 'mip_Audio_Article'
          });
      });
    }
      

  })(document);
</script>

<script id="gtm-mip-engagement-timer" type="text/javascript">
    (function(document, window, undefined) {
        var addEvent = {{fn.addEvent}};
        var removeEvent = {{fn.removeEvent}};
    
        var counter = 0;
        var resetTimeoutEvents = ['mousemove', 'touchstart', 'scroll', 'keydown'];
        var engagementInterval,
            engagementTimeout,
            hidden, 
            visibilityChange;
    
        // Vendor fill
        if (typeof document.hidden !== "undefined") {
    
          // Opera 12.10 and Firefox 18 and later support 
          hidden = "hidden";
          visibilityChange = "visibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.mozHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "mozHidden";
          visibilityChange = "mozvisibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.msHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "msHidden";
          visibilityChange = "msvisibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.webkitHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "webkitHidden";
          visibilityChange = "webkitvisibilitychange";
          
        }
    
        setEngagementTimeout();
        registerTimeoutEvents();
        setEngagementInterval();
    
        if(visibilityChange) {
          
          addEvent(document, visibilityChange, function() {
    
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
    
            if(!document[hidden]) {
    
              setEngagementInterval();
    
            }
    
          });
    
        } else {
          
          addEvent(window, 'blur', function() {
    
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
    
          });
    
          addEvent(window, 'focus', function() {
    
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
            setEngagementInterval();
    
          });
    
        }
    
        function registerTimeoutEvents() {
    
          for(i = resetTimeoutEvents.length; i > -1; i--) {
    
            var _event = resetTimeoutEvents[i];
            addEvent(window, _event, resetEngagementTimeout);
    
          }
    
        }
    
        function setEngagementInterval() {
    
          engagementInterval = setInterval(function() {
    
            counter++;
            window[{{MIP Data Layer Name}}].push({
              'event': 'engagementTimer',
              'attributes': {
                'counter': counter * 15
              }
            });
    
          }, Number({{Engagement Timer Interval Milliseconds}}) );
    
        }
    
        function setEngagementTimeout() {
            
          engagementTimeout = setTimeout(function() {
            
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
            engagementInterval = false;
    
          }, Number({{Engagement Timer Idle Milliseconds}}) + 1 );
    
        }
    
        function resetEngagementTimeout() {
    
          // Clear our events
          for(i = resetTimeoutEvents.length; i > -1; i--) {
    
            var _event = resetTimeoutEvents[i];
            removeEvent(window, _event, resetEngagementTimeout);
    
          }
    
          setTimeout(function() {
    
            // Re-register our idle reset events in one seconds
            registerTimeoutEvents();
    
          }, 1500);
    
          if(!engagementInterval) {
    
            setEngagementInterval();
    
          }
    
          clearTimeout(setEngagementTimeout);
          setEngagementTimeout();
    
        }

    })(document, window);
</script>

          var _docHeight = parseInt(docHeight, 10);
          var _scrollOffset = parseInt(scrollOffset, 10);
          var _supplemental = parseInt(supplemental, 10);

            '50%' : (_docHeight - _scrollOffset) * 0.50 + _scrollOffset,

          }
          
          return _marks;
        }

          // Check each active mark

              cache.push(key);
            }
          });
        }

          var scrollOffset = options.topElementSelector ? $(options.topElementSelector).offset(top) : 0;
	
		    if({{Is Article}}) {
